"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-chad-le-clos-says-tatjana-smith-is-our-michael-phelps\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbChad Le Clos says Tatjana Smith is our Michael Phelps  Chad Le Clos believes that Tatjana Smith is a level above the competition in the pool just like record-breaking Olympian Michael Phelps.  Chad Le Clos believes that Tatjana Smith is a level above the competition just like record-breaking Olympian Michael Phelps.  Le Clos praised Smith's determination and hard work to get to the top given the resources at her disposal.  \\\"I am glad for her. She's also home-grown. We have got three 50m pools in South Africa and we have produced four Olympic champions since 1996. I told (her coach) Rocco and Tatjana in 2019 that she'd do what she's doing. She's a lovely person. She's too good for these girls, she's like Phelps.\\\"  Le Clos was able to take a gold medal off of Phelps himself, but says that he wasn't ready for what would come after that.  He recalled what Phelps said to him inLondon 2012: \\\"\\\"I am passing the torch to you now, enjoy the moment. I am going to be watching your career.\\\"  Le Clos believes that he wasn't 'supposed' to win that race in 2012 but feels that 2016 was a different story.  He feels that losing to someone who was subsequently sanctioned for doping is a mark on the sport.  \\\"I wasn't supposed to win that race,\\\" he said of London  \\\"If we had swum that race a hundred times, if we could replay it like a Fifa game, Phelps would win it 97, 98 times. Then again, in 2016, I'd win that 200m freestyle 95 out of a hundred times. I should have two golds and two silvers. That race still haunts me. I hate myself for that race. Plus, the gold medallist (Sun Yang) is a drug cheat. He's been banned for doping. But, swimming is full of politics. His country is a lot bigger than South Africa. It would take a lot for the authorities to strip him and hand me the gold.\\\"  Le Clos believes that swimming's Olympic focus means that many forget what happens between the games.  \\\"I have always wanted to go down as the best. Have I under-achieved? No. I have over-achieved. Let us play this back. From 2012 I over-achieved. I beat Phelps. I had the world at my feet. I followed up by winning double gold at the 2013 world championships. At the 2014 Commonwealth Games I won seven medals. In 2015 at the world champs I won gold and silver. At Rio 2016 the silver should have been gold. In 2017 I was world champ again and at the 2018 Commonwealth Games I won five medals. I have also won 20 world short-course championship medals, the second most in the history of swimming. Only Ryan Lochte has won more and I need three more medals (or two gold) to overtake him as short-course swimming GOAT. Then you have Phelps and myself as swimming's two GOATS. How could that be under-achieving?  \\\"I think people tend to look at the Olympics every four years and forget everything else. As I said, with respect, I am a pensioner. I know I will have to make a decision as to when to stop, but my immediate future after Paris is breaking Lochte's all-time record at the world short-course championships in Budapest in December. Then, it would be the 2026 Commonwealth Games. I have already won 18 medals there, even more than Ian Thorpe. Who knows what happens after that?\\\"  Let us know by clicking on the comment tab below this article or by emailinginfo@thesouthafrican.comor sending a WhatsApp to 060 011 021 1. You can also follow@TheSAnews on XandThe South African on Facebookfor the latest news.  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"